  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--interview with Eva Weiss, November 16, 1995, tape number 3.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Life in a ghetto was also-- well, that's-- already, we faced up to it, that something terrible is happening to us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they're going to ship the Jews out of their country, and never be no more Jews in Hungary, and all that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- you know, and then my father heard the stories.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now they started to believe that this is must've been how it was in Poland, and how it was in Czechoslovakia, and all over in Russia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at the-- at the ghetto, when we went into the building, we-- family, and even so, we knew all the people in Olaszliszka, all the Jews-- sort of all wanted to stick together.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my uncle, my aunt, and three girls-- four girls, and a son, was with the same building, same room with us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, if I remember correctly, my father-- [SIGHS] the men went to take the next bedroom.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all the women, we were sleeping together on the floor, no bed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Just-- and I think that we must have took some pillows, or, or their pillows, a blanket.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Anyway, we're laying in bed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the two women-- no, three, because our next-door neighbor we took with us to there because their daughter escaped.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I'd like to chase back a little bit how this particular next-door neighbor came over to us, just before we go into the synagogue and gather the Jews, that his three daughters, with, with gentile paper, escaping from going to anywhere we go, ghetto or what-- and came over, middle of the night Saturday night, to my father.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He knocks on a-- on a window from the roof.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Somehow he climbed over.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
